==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scapulo-
<hw>Scap"u*lo-</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>A combining form used in
anatomy to indicate <xex>connection with</xex>, or <xex>relation
to</xex>, <xex>the scapula</xex> or <xex>the shoulder</xex>; <as>as, the
<ex>scapulo</ex>-clavicular articulation, the articulation between the
scapula and clavicle</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapus</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
